approvedSignatureCheckers(bytes32).details: Returns the list of approved signature checkers for `keyHash`.

callCheckerInfos(bytes32).details: Returns the list of call checker infos.

canExecute(bytes32,address,bytes).details: Returns whether a key hash can execute a call. Note: Does NOT coalesce a zero-address `target` to `address(this)`.

canExecutePackedInfos(bytes32).details: Returns an array of packed (`target`, `fnSel`) that `keyHash` is authorized to execute on. - `target` is in the upper 20 bytes. - `fnSel` is in the lower 4 bytes.

checkAndIncrementNonce(uint256).details: Checks current nonce and increments the sequence for the `seqKey`.

computeDigest((address,uint256,bytes)[],.details: Computes the EIP712 digest for `calls`. If the the nonce starts with `MULTICHAIN_NONCE_PREFIX`, the digest will be computed without the chain ID. Otherwise, the digest will be computed with the chain ID.

execute(bytes32,bytes).details: Executes the calls in `executionData`. Reverts and bubbles up error if any call fails. `executionData` encoding (single batch): - If `opData` is empty, `executionData` is simply `abi.encode(calls)`. - Else, `executionData` is `abi.encode(calls, opData)`.   See: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-7579 `executionData` encoding (batch of batches): - `executionData` is `abi.encode(bytes[])`, where each element in `bytes[]`   is an `executionData` for a single batch. Supported modes: - `0x01000000000000000000...`: Single batch. Does not support optional `opData`. - `0x01000000000078210001...`: Single batch. Supports optional `opData`. - `0x01000000000078210002...`: Batch of batches. For the "batch of batches" mode, each batch will be recursively passed into `execute` internally with mode `0x01000000000078210001...`. Useful for passing in batches signed by different signers. Authorization checks: - If `opData` is empty, the implementation SHOULD require that   `msg.sender == address(this)`. - If `opData` is not empty, the implementation SHOULD use the signature   encoded in `opData` to determine if the caller can perform the execution. - If `msg.sender` is an authorized entry point, then `execute` MAY accept   calls from the entry point, and MAY use `opData` for specialized logic. `opData` may be used to store additional data for authentication, paymaster data, gas limits, etc.

getContextKeyHash().details: Return the key hash that signed the latest execution context.Returns bytes32(0) if the EOA key was used.

getKey(bytes32).details: Returns the key corresponding to the `keyHash`. Reverts if the key does not exist.

getKeys().details: Returns arrays of all (non-expired) authorized keys and their hashes.

getNonce(uint192).details: Return current nonce with sequence key.

hash((uint40,uint8,bool,bytes)).details: Returns the hash of the key, which does not includes the expiry.

invalidateNonce(uint256).details: Increments the sequence for the `seqKey` in nonce (i.e. upper 192 bits). This invalidates the nonces for the `seqKey`, up to (inclusive) `uint64(nonce)`.

isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes).details: Checks if a signature is valid. Note: For security reasons, we can only let this function validate against the original EOA key and other super admin keys. Otherwise, any session key can be used to approve infinite allowances via Permit2 by default, which will allow apps infinite power.Note: The rehashing scheme is not EIP-5267 compliant. A different domain separator is used for the rehashing, which excludes `name` and `version` from the domain, for latency improvements offchain.

keyAt(uint256).details: Returns the authorized key at index `i`.

keyCount().details: Returns the number of authorized keys.

removeSpendLimit(bytes32,address,uint8).details: Removes the spend limit of `token` for `keyHash` for `period`.

setCallChecker(bytes32,address,address).details: Sets a third party call checker, which has a view function `canExecute(bytes32,address,bytes)` to return if a call can be executed. By setting `checker` to `address(0)`, it removes the it from the list of call checkers on this account. The `ANY_KEYHASH` and `ANY_TARGET` wildcards apply here too.

setCanExecute(bytes32,address,bytes4,boo.details: Sets the ability of a key hash to execute a call with a function selector. Note: Does NOT coalesce a zero-address `target` to `address(this)`.

setSignatureCheckerApproval(bytes32,addr.details: Sets whether `checker` can use `isValidSignature` to successfully validate a signature for a given key hash.

setSpendLimit(bytes32,address,uint8,uint.details: Sets the spend limit of `token` for `keyHash` for `period`.

spendAndExecuteInfos(bytes32[]).details: Returns spend and execute infos for each provided key hash in the same order.

spendInfos(bytes32).details: Returns an array containing information on all the spends for `keyHash`.

startOfSpendPeriod(uint256,uint8).details: Rounds the unix timestamp down to the period.

supportsExecutionMode(bytes32).details: Provided for execution mode support detection.

unwrapAndValidateSignature(bytes32,bytes.details: Returns if the signature is valid, along with its `keyHash`. The `signature` is a wrapped signature, given by `abi.encodePacked(bytes(innerSignature), bytes32(keyHash), bool(prehash))`.

upgradeHook(bytes32).details: For this very first version, the upgrade hook is just an no-op. Provided to enable calling it via plain Solidity. For future implementations, we will have an upgrade hook which can contain logic to migrate storage on a case-by-case basis if needed. If this hook is implemented to mutate storage, it MUST check that `_UPGRADE_HOOK_GUARD_TRANSIENT_SLOT` is correctly set.

upgradeProxyAccount(address).details: Upgrades the proxy account. If this account is delegated directly without usage of EIP7702Proxy, this operation will not affect the logic until the authority is redelegated to a proper EIP7702Proxy. The `newImplementation` should implement `upgradeProxyAccount` or similar, otherwise upgrades will be locked and only a new EIP-7702 transaction can change the authority's logic.
